body:
Hi @mgrigajtis,
What error do you get in logs?
Can I contact you on some messenger?  I really like this app, it has a much better interface than all the other and I'd like to work with you.
Maybe I'll try to get this thing running on a Raspberry Pi.  If I run into the same problem I'll report it here.
Are you using python3.6 as answered in your first post ? OctoBot is only working on python3.8

Trying to install in Raspberry Pi with python 3.9 it's hanging while trying to install OctoBot-Commons-1.6.2.tar.gz.

I will install Python 3.8 and try again.
All the errors for the Windows version was from the executable, and not dependent on any version of Python.
There is no binary available for pi.
Is it a pi3 or a pi4 ?
Your commons build failed because it requires rust to be installed in your system.
Installed Rust which was painful on a Pi 3B+.  Commons installed, but the next library failed to build.

> No

Did you retry with the latest version?
I have not, but I will have to try when I get some free time to revisit this.
